    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="724"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/760</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-20T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 21, 11.41 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1257. In conference just concluded, Minister for Foreign Affairs brought up
                    subject matter, article 13, Spanish-American commercial agreement of March 7. He
                    said that Spanish Ambassador in Washington, had informed him that some one now
                    in Europe would be sent here shortly to negotiate further agreement as provided
                    in article under consideration. He was informed that Embassy had similar
                    instructions and that he would be further informed immediately upon the arrival
                    here of such party. He replied that he would then designate a conferee on the
                    part of Spain and that negotiations could proceed at once, and added that he
                    hoped the Government of the United States, pending such negotiations, would not
                    change its policy in regard to the question thus to be considered. He was
                    informed that Embassy was of opinion that no change in such policy would be made
                    until an opportunity was had for proposed negotiations. Embassy awaits
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
